</span></span></span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">]</span></span> <span class="mjx-mo MJXc-space3"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.077em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">=</span></span> <span class="mjx-mn MJXc-space3"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.372em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">0.8750</span></span> <span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em; padding-right: 0.036em;">ν</span></span> <span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em; padding-right: 0.085em;">N</span></span> <span class="mjx-mo MJXc-space2"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.298em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">+</span></span> <span class="mjx-mn MJXc-space2"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.372em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">0.3137</span></span> <span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em; padding-right: 0.036em;">ν</span></span> <span class="mjx-mo MJXc-space2"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.298em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">+</span></span> <span class="mjx-mn MJXc-space2"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.372em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">1.0</span></span> <span class="mjx-mo MJXc-space2"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.298em; padding-bottom: 0.446em;">+</span></span> <span class="mjx-mn MJXc-space2"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.372em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">0.6275</span></span> <span class="mjx-texatom"><span class="mjx-mrow"><span class="mjx-mo"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.593em;">/</span></span></span></span> <span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em; padding-right: 0.085em;">N</span></span></span></span></span></span></span> </p><figure class="image image_resized" style="width:74.96%"><img src="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/ogcEgWEgmzBw8ePMC/v8kegffip7w1si8iitps" srcset="https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/ogcEgWEgmzBw8ePMC/vsqaskbhbkl66tssvzgs 210w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/ogcEgWEgmzBw8ePMC/bhjsjznanndaw65p1swm 420w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/ogcEgWEgmzBw8ePMC/bugxsdysrzhehpecyqt5 630w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/ogcEgWEgmzBw8ePMC/wzyoxlewxarlk9uyxmps 840w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/ogcEgWEgmzBw8ePMC/lnr93ksrclvqygwcjkhr 1050w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/ogcEgWEgmzBw8ePMC/sylukz6wxe4upclgwkpi 1260w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/ogcEgWEgmzBw8ePMC/lk3yjwknkhbvmrxatk3l 1470w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/ogcEgWEgmzBw8ePMC/wgxqgudzrlugg01tl9vm 1680w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/ogcEgWEgmzBw8ePMC/yk4dwjz5kkefofkpbehy 1890w, https://res.cloudinary.com/lesswrong-2-0/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/v1/mirroredImages/ogcEgWEgmzBw8ePMC/p4pfudyeojrhgdliyods 2060w"><figcaption>如果您选择红色或蓝色，则预期效用作为玩家数量的函数。使选择蓝色变得明智所需的玩家数量取决于你的利他主义<span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="\nu"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em; padding-right: 0.036em;">ν</span></span></span></span></span></span></span> ，即你对相对于自己的陌生人的重视程度。</figcaption></figure><p>这里的常数项是你自己生存的概率（以及预期效用）。</p><p>第二项与你对他人生命相对于你自己的生命的价值<span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="\nu"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em; padding-right: 0.036em;">ν</span></span></span></span></span></span></span>成正比，来自于你可能进行决胜一票的可能性：这里<span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="N"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em; padding-right: 0.085em;">N</span></span></span></span></span></span></span>被抵消，因为随着概率的降低，你可以拯救的人数会增加，因此选择蓝色因果关系平均可以节省大约 1/3 的人的时间 (0.6275-0.3137)。 （最后一项也与决胜局有关，但随着<span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="N"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em; padding-right: 0.085em;">N</span></span></span></span></span></span></span>变大，它会消失，无论如何，这两种情况都是相同的。）</p><p>第一项与<span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="N"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em; padding-right: 0.085em;">N</span></span></span></span></span></span></span>成正比，代表通过因果关系使他人受益的潜力，显然如果您选择蓝色，则效果会更大。只要<span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="\nu > 0"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em; padding-right: 0.036em;">ν</span></span> <span class="mjx-mo MJXc-space3"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">>;</span></span> <span class="mjx-mn MJXc-space3"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.372em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">0</span></span></span></span></span></span></span> ，随着玩家数量的增加，该项最终将压倒其他因素，这意味着任何关心（线性）其他人的人都应该选择蓝色作为较大的<span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="N"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em; padding-right: 0.085em;">N</span></span></span></span></span></span></span>值。</p><p><strong>综上所述：</strong></p><p><strong>如果玩家数量至少是你愿意拯救的最小人数的 2-3 倍，你会想要选择蓝色。</strong></p><ul><li>对于 ν=0.1：如果 N >; 22.01，则选择蓝色</li><li>对于 ν=0.01：如果 N >; 261.44，则选择蓝色</li><li>对于 ν=0.001：如果 N >; 2655.73，则选择蓝色</li></ul><p>我发现这个结果非常违反直觉。这也让我很混蛋，因为我最初选择了红色。但让我试着稍微变蓝一点。我认为这个论点是这样的：红色可以帮助你个人生存。但在一个偏向蓝色的社会中，平均而言，有更多的人能够生存下来。如果有足够多的人面临生命危险，那么让社会变得更蓝一点将比你自己的生命风险更重要。</p><p>说实话，我不知道我是否有勇气根据令人毛骨悚然的相关性来选择 18% 的死亡几率。 </p><p></p><ol class="footnotes" role="doc-endnotes"><li class="footnote-item" role="doc-endnote" id="fns4iy3ko6k4e"> <span class="footnote-back-link"><sup><strong><a href="#fnrefs4iy3ko6k4e">^</a></strong></sup></span><div class="footnote-content"><p>如果你的效用是幸存者数量的对数怎么办？我认为这不会有太大区别，因为那样你还必须考虑到世界上每个玩得不好的人。 If <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="N"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em; padding-right: 0.085em;">N</span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is less than about a billion, your marginal utility over those <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="N"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em; padding-right: 0.085em;">N</span></span></span></span></span></span></span> people will still be roughly linear. If you would choose blue under that linear marginal utility for <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="N=1"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em; padding-right: 0.085em;">N</span></span> <span class="mjx-mo MJXc-space3"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.077em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">=</span></span> <span class="mjx-mn MJXc-space3"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.372em; padding-bottom: 0.372em;">1</span></span></span></span></span></span></span> billion, then increasing <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="N"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em; padding-right: 0.085em;">N</span></span></span></span></span></span></span> should not change your mind. If you would choose red for <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="N="><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.446em; padding-bottom: 0.298em; padding-right: 0.085em;">N</span></span> <span class="mjx-mo MJXc-space3"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R" style="padding-top: 0.077em; padding-bottom: 0.298em;">=</span></span></span></span></span></span></span> 1 billion, it&#39;s because your value for altruism <span><span class="mjpage"><span class="mjx-chtml"><span class="mjx-math" aria-label="\nu"><span class="mjx-mrow" aria-hidden="true"><span class="mjx-mi"><span class="mjx-char MJXc-TeX-math-I" style="padding-top: 0.225em; padding-bottom: 0.298em; padding-right: 0.036em;">ν</span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is very close to zero, and you were probably going to choose red no matter what.</p></div></li></ol><br/><br/> <a href="https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/ogcEgWEgmzBw8ePMC/red-pill-vs-blue-pill-bayes-style#comments">Discuss</a> ; https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/ogcEgWEgmzBw8ePMC/red-pill-vs-blue-pill-bayes-style ogcEgWEgmzBw8ePMCErickBall Wed, 16 Aug 2023 15:23:24 GMT 
What does it mean to “trust science”?Published on August 16, 2023 2:56 PM GMT<br/><br/><blockquote><p> <i>And this, my children, is why we do not say things like “I believe in science”. I mean, don&#39;t get me wrong, science definitely exists—I&#39;ve seen it. But not everything that calls itself science is science, and even good science sometimes gets wrong results. –</i> <a href="https://twitter.com/asymmetricinfo/status/1684701303463714821"><i>Megan McArdle</i></a></p></blockquote><p> Should we “trust science” or “believe in science”?</p><p> I think this is a fuzzy idea that we would do well to make clear and precise. What does it mean to “trust science?”</p><p> Does it mean “trust scientists”? Which scientists? They disagree, often vehemently. Which statements of theirs? Surely not all of them; scientists do not speak <i>ex cathedra</i> for “Science.”</p><p> Does it mean “trust scientific institutions”? Again, which ones?</p><p> Does it mean “trust scientific papers”? Any one paper can be wrong in its conclusions or even its methods. The study itself could have been mistaken, or the writeup might not reflect the study.</p><p> And it certainly can&#39;t mean “trust science news,” which is <a href="https://twitter.com/jasoncrawford/status/1662142462524112908">notoriously inaccurate</a> .</p><p> More charitably, it could mean “trust the scientific process,” if that is properly understood to mean not some rigid Scientific Method but a rational process of observation, measurement, evidence, logic, debate, and iterative revision of concepts and theories. Even in that case, though, what we should <i>trust</i> is not the particular output of the scientific process at any given time. It can make wrong turns. Instead, we should trust that it will find the truth eventually, and that it is our best and only method for doing so.</p><p> The motto of science is not “trust us.” (!) The true motto of science is the opposite. It is that of the Royal Society: <i>nullius in verba</i> , or roughly: “take no one&#39;s word.”</p><p> There is no capital-S Science—a new authority to substitute for God or King. There is only science, which is nothing more or less than the human faculty of reason exercised deliberately, systematically, methodically, meticulously to discover general knowledge about the world.</p><p> So when someone laments a lack of “trust” in science today, what do they mean? Do they mean placing religion over science, faith over reason? Do they mean the growing distrust of elites and institutions, a sort of folksy populism that dismisses education and expertise in general? Or do they mean “you have to follow my favored politician / political program, because Science”? (That&#39;s the one to watch out for. Physics, chemistry and biology can point out problems, but we need history, economics and philosophy to solve them.)</p><p> Anyway, here&#39;s to science—the system that asks you not to trust, but to <i>think</i> . </p><figure class="media"><div data-oembed-url="https://youtu.be/OL6-x0modwY"><div><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/OL6-x0modwY" allow="autoplay; encrypted-media" allowfullscreen=""></iframe></div></div></figure><p> <i>Adapted from</i> <a href="https://twitter.com/jasoncrawford/status/1192851511023325184"><i>a 2019 Twitter thread</i></a> <i>.</i></p><br/><br/> <a href="https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/RkrntNZsGtBMg765K/what-does-it-mean-to-trust-science#comments">Discuss</a> ; https://www.lesswrong.com/posts/RkrntNZsGtBMg765K/what-does-it-mean-to-trust-science RkrntNZsGtBMg765Kjasoncrawford Wed, 16 Aug 2023 14:56:20 GMT 
